Hitter Evaluation Report - Condon, Charlie

  • Player Summary: Condon, Charlie

Hitter Notes Right-handed hitting corner infielder/outfielder from the University of Georgia. An elite power threat, he hit 62 home runs in 113 games as a Bulldog and earned the 2024 Golden Spikes Award. Consistently makes hard contact and shows advanced plate discipline, rarely chasing—particularly against breaking balls. Primarily a pull hitter, but demonstrates the ability to drive the ball with authority to right-center field as well.
